RADULA (n = 3). Comprises 95 transverse rows with 57–61 teeth per row; radular formula: (20)-(8–10)- 1-(8–10)-(20). Central tooth symmetric, unicuspid, tongue-shaped; lateral teeth longer than central tooth and oblique, unicuspid, tongue-shaped (
Fig. 6A
). Marginal teeth tricuspid with medium-sized endocone; mesocone rather large, with rounded cusp; ectocone triangular (
Fig. 6B–C
).
